{
  "texts": [
    "The encoderdecoder paradigm has recently become a standard architecture of neural machine translation.",
    "The input language sequences from source texts are first encoded into real number vectors and then decoded into output language sequences.",
    "To address the problem of machine translations barely using pronouns or other forms of wording to replace repeated words, external linguistic knowledge, like knowledge about reference relations, can be integrated into either the encoder or decoder of the machine translation models.",
    "This integration can facilitate MT models better capturing the semantic links among different language units in a particular context.",
    "The second solution is an internal one for machine translation models."
  ]
}